HEADWORD: Spermatogonium
<hw>Sper`ma*to*go"ni*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/, <?/<?/<?/, sperm + <?/<?/<?/ offspring.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A primitive seminal cell, occurring in masses
in the seminal tubules. It divides into a mass (spermosphere) of small
cells (spermoblast), which in turn give rise to spermatozoids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spermatoid</ent>⟦br⟧
